<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Ragefire, the new Shards/Fragements and my experiences. <br>
<br>
First of all, I think this is a VERY good change. It completely eliminates the competitive nature over a single bottleneck on an insane timer. I gave up on my Epic just because I wasn’t going to put up with the Ragefire crap. Every other Ragefire had drama and bad will attached to it and I wasn’t going to deal with that. <br>
<br>
Anyway… I spent about 12 hours, give or take, in Skyfire gathering the Pearlescent Fragments. They look like Pearls, are No Drop and labelled CLR / Human, High Elf, Erudite etc. only. They weight 6.0 each <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   From my experiences, they can drop off of most, if not all, the mobs in the zone. I got Fragments from a Mature Wurm, an Old Wurm, a Mature or Elder Wyvern (can’t remember which), and a Skyfire Drake. I had anywhere from 1 person to 7 other people helping me at all times and we just pulled stuff (avoiding those God awful Chromo-Drakes) and killed it all. They seemed totally random, I went for 6 hours without a single Fragment dropping and then got 2 Fragements within 10 mintues of each other. This was done in 2 shifts, I spent awhile yesterday (Sept 4) camping these things and got 2. Got my other 2 today (Sept 5). <br>
<br>
As stated, these drop from most, if not all, mobs in the zone but my groups setup our camp near Veeshan’s Peak for several reasons: <br>
<br>
1. The area around Veeshan’s Peak is higher in level than other areas in the zone with 90% of the mobs Dark Blue to Level 60. I don’t know if higher mobs have a better chance to drop Fragments or not, but it seemed a safe bet. <br>
<br>
2. The area around Veeshan’s Peak is totally safe. If you are facing the entrance, we set up camp outside the tunnel to the right (had our backs to the wall). There were roamers here but not many and you can, normally, see them coming a mile away. If we needed to med or CR (Guardian Wurm got us once), we just moved to the top of the Peak where it is 99% safe (won’t say completely safe but in my VP raids and wipeouts, I’ve never seen a mob path on top of the peak). <br>
<br>
3. There were NO other people around. There were upwards of 70 people in the zone last night and everyone else seemed to be setting up camp on the wall from where the Warder spawns (Rage’s old spawn spot) to the Druid portal in spot. All night people were bitching and moaning about being pulled over, KS’d etc. Meanwhile, my group was doing non-stop pulls without a single person nearby to get in our way (or vice versa). <br>
<br>
During this stay, there was a share of “opportunists” or as I like to refer to them, slime that is lower than dirt. Most of these people didn’t stick around too long but they were, typically, solo Druids and Necromancers looking to stir up trouble by “claiming” to have destroyed 3 Shards in the last 15 minutes or those attempting to sell “looting rights” for potential Shard Drops. Most of these people didn’t last too long as the whole zone was against them. There were a lot of solo kiters here who expressed disappointment that “their” zone was being invaded but for the most part they just moved out of people’s way and continued to exp there. In fact this was who I got my first Fragement. A soloer dropped a mob with a Fragement on the West Wall and shouted out the /loc. Once again, the advantage of hunting by VP came into play since everyone else was near zone borders and nowhere near the Fragement. I was easily able to scoot over there and snatch it up. <br>
<br>
Now, my thoughts are that, in all honesty, the Fragements might be a bit too common right now. I did it in 12 hours but only had 1.5 groups at the most. Fragements are pretty much in line for this style setup, though I lean towards being too common, but when you have Guilds bringing in 20 – 40 people, they can get a set of Fragements within an hour or two just by wholesale slaughter. I’ll admit, I went after my Fragements fast because I fear a drop rate nerf incoming. I’ll be VERY surprised if Verant views the drop rate as being where they want it. <br>
<br>
Overall though, it’s a VERY good change. It does make the Epic a LOT easier but it’s still not the easiest. A higher level guild can push a Cleric through the entire Epic in a weekend. A lower level Guild is still going to get hung up with Ixiblat and the Overking. Neither of those events are what I would call “trivial.” They’re not hard for a well equipped Guild but for a smaller Guild, they both represent some serious challenges. <br>
<br>
Oh, Ragefire is exactly the same. He lasted, exactly 10 seconds since I had 3 Manaburn Guildies with me.<br>
<br>
